Group institution names only when they clearly refer to the same U.S. bank or credit union.

Group:

- Legal name and common operating name for the same institution, e.g. "Newburyport Five Cents Savings Bank" and "Newburyport Bank" when context makes the alias clear.
- Minor suffix, punctuation, capitalization, or charter-designator variants, e.g. "Barksdale Federal Credit Union" and "Barksdale FCU".
- Rebrand or short-name variants when they are unmistakably the same institution.

Do not group:

- Different institutions with similar names, e.g. "Horizon Bank" and "First Horizon Bank".
- A bank holding company with a separately named bank unless the value clearly denotes the same bank.
- A product name, product family, login domain, app name, or vendor name with an institution.
- Institutions in different states with a shared generic name unless the values themselves provide enough context to confirm identity.
